IBADAN – The former governor of Oyo State and Osi Olubdan of Ibadanland, High Chief Rasidi Ladoja, has said that all controversies surrounding the chief­taincy and enthronement of the next Olubadan of Ibadanland have been re­solved. Chief Ladoja said this while briefing journal­ists on Saturday on the outcome of a closed-door meeting with the members of Olubadan-in-Council had with Governor Seyi Makinde at the Govern­ment House Lodge, Agodi, Ibadan. Ladoja also affirmed the candidature of Otun Olubadan of Ibadan Land, High Chief Lekan Balo­gun as the next Olubadan of Ibadan, adding that the Ibadan high chiefs had resolved their differences and very united to instal Balogun as the next Ol­ubadan. Leaders’ Honesty Will Check Security Challenges – Bishop Eichie IPOB Allays Fears Of Lockdown In South-East, Announces… Among the members of Olubadan-in-Council that attended the meeting, were High Chief Lekan Balogun, High Chief Owolabi Olaku­leyin, High Chief Gbada­mosi Adebimpe, and High Chief Eddy Oyewole.